FT  01 FEB 93 / Ex-Mirror editor goes to Today
MR RICHARD Stott, former editor of the Daily Mirror, is to replace Mr Martin
Dunn as editor of Today, News International, the newspaper group, announced
last night. Mr Dunn is to edit the group's Boston Herald.
Mr Stott was sacked as Mirror editor in November by Mr David Montgomery, the
new chief executive of Mirror Group Newspapers. Mr Montgomery used to edit
Today.
